content: <articles>    <article xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink/">   <front>     <article-meta>       <title-group>         <article-title>Dartmouth Stellar Evolution Grids</article-title>       </title-group>       <contrib-group>         <contrib contrib-type="author">           <name>             <surname>Morton</surname>             <given-names>Timothy</given-names>           </name>         </contrib>       </contrib-group>       <pub-date pub-type="pub">         <year>2015</year>       </pub-date>       <self-uri xlink:href="http://zenodo.org/record/15843"/>       <self-uri xlink:href="https://zenodo.org/record/15843/files/dartmouth.tri"/>       <self-uri xlink:href="https://zenodo.org/record/15843/files/dartmouth.h5"/>     </article-meta>     <abstract><p>Dartmouth stellar model grids, used by the &#39;isochrones&#39; python package (github.com/timothydmorton/isochrones).&nbsp; Update from previous grids; these now include WISE bands, ages &lt; 1Gyr, and have coarser Fe/H sampling.</p></abstract>   </front>   <article-type>user-zenodo</article-type> </article>   </articles>
